            <h3>Sulphonamides</h3>
            <p>A synthetic antimicrobial produced entirely by chemicals rather than a naturally-produced antibiotic, sulphonamides are a broad-spectrum class of treatments with variants that can also be effective against non-infectious diseases like diabetes. Folic acid synthesis inhibitors, they prevent bacteria from producing DNA, which disrupts cell growth and division, controlling infections. Sulphonamides can also be used against many fungal and parasitic infections, and some which also disrupt other non-folate cell functions like microtubule assembly can be potentially used against cancer as well.</p>
